<h2 id="peanut-butter-chocolate-chip-cookies">Peanut Butter Chocolate Chip Cookies</h2>

<p>Ingredients:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">50 grams</code> glucose</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">225 grams</code> bread flour</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">2 grams</code> baking powder</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">1 gram</code> baking soda</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">9 grams</code> kosher salt</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">1 Â½ sticks</code> unsalted butter (room temperature)</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">300 grams</code> granulated sugar</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">260 grams</code> creamy peanut butter</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">2</code> large eggs</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">Â½ gram</code> vanilla extract</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">4-6 ounces</code> high-quality dark chocolate or chocolate chips</li>
</ul>

<p>Steps:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Whisk together <code class="highlighter-rouge">flour</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">baking soda</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">baking powder</code>, and <code class="highlighter-rouge">salt</code>.</li>
  <li>Put <code class="highlighter-rouge">butter</code>, <code class="highlighter-rouge">sugar</code>, and <code class="highlighter-rouge">glucose</code> in a bowl.</li>
  <li>Beat on medium-high for 2-3 minutes until light and fluffy.</li>
  <li>Scrape sides of the bowl and add the <code class="highlighter-rouge">peanut butter</code>, mix to combine, ~30s</li>
  <li>Add the 2 <code class="highlighter-rouge">eggs</code> one at a time while mixing until combined, ~30s</li>
  <li>Add <code class="highlighter-rouge">vanilla</code> and beat on high for 3 minutes until light, creamy, and doubled in volume</li>
  <li>Scrape sides of the bowl and add the dry ingredients, mixing on low until just combined, ~30s</li>
  <li>Mix in Chocolate chips</li>
  <li>wrap dough in plastic wrap in a tube shape with a cookie sized cross-section</li>
  <li>Refrigerate overnight, and up to 3-5 days</li>
</ol>

<p>Baking Steps:</p>
<ol>
  <li>When ready, preheat oven to 350â„‰</li>
  <li>Link cookie tray with silicon pad, parchment paper, or foil</li>
  <li>Pull cookie tube from the fridge and cut cookies out of the tube, placing 6-8 per tray</li>
  <li>Bake for 15-18min, rotating them after the first 5min and checking every few minutes starting at the 
10 minute mark</li>
</ol>

